<p><img alt="" src="/public/uploads/images/curtinsingaporegroupofstudentsonbench.jpg" style="height:394px; width:700px" /></p>

<p><strong>Training Work Permit</strong></p>

<p>The Training Work Permit (TWP) is for</p>

<p style="margin-left:35.45pt">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Semi-skilled or unskilled employees from related overseas companies to undergo training in Singapore.</p>

<p style="margin-left:35.45pt">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Foreign students studying in private educational institutions (PEIs) in Singapore.</p>

<p>The TWP is valid for up to six months and employers of TWP holder will incur levy. Approval is also subjected to the company&rsquo;s quota availability.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Training Employment Pass</strong></p>

<p>The Training Employment Pass (TEP) is for corporate trainees from overseas undergoing practical training in Singapore for professional, managerial, executive or specialist jobs for their eventual work back in their own country. The TEP is also applicable to foreign undergraduates who wish to gain internship experience to augment their study.</p>

<p>These foreigners may be eligible for the Training Employment Pass, valid up to three months:</p>

<p style="margin-left:35.45pt">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Undergraduates - The training attachment in Singapore must be part of the undergraduate&#39;s Degree programme from an&nbsp;<a href="http://www.mom.gov.sg/foreign-manpower/passes-visas/training-employment/before-you-apply/Pages/Institutions.aspx" target="_blank">acceptable institution</a></p>

<p style="margin-left:35.45pt">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Trainees from foreign offices or subsidiaries</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:872px">
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="height:185px; width:1px">
			<p>&nbsp;</p>
			</td>
			<td style="height:185px; width:600px">
			<p><strong>Sources</strong></p>

			<p>SETC provides interns from the following countries:</p>

			<ul>
				<li>Philippine</li>
				<li>India</li>
				<li>Vietnam</li>
			</ul>

			<p><strong>Documents</strong></p>

			<p>Intern needs to submit:</p>

			<ul>
				<li>Resume with full body photograph.</li>
				<li>Passport copy (Personal particulars page).</li>
				<li>Letter for education institution stating your matriculation status (For undergraduates)</li>
				<li>Education certificate and transcripts (For graduates)</li>
				<li>TWP/TEP Application Form</li>
			</ul>

			<p><strong>Application Process</strong></p>

			<ul>
				<li>Step 1 &ndash; Intern submit documents to SETC for assessment and verification.</li>
				<li>Step 2 &ndash; SETC presents application to prospective employers.</li>
				<li>Step 3 &ndash; Intern attends selection interview.</li>
				<li>Step 4 &ndash; Employer applies TWP/TEP with MOM.</li>
				<li>Step 5 &ndash; Intern pays Placement Service Fee (TBA) and commences internship with employer.</li>
			</ul>

			<p><strong>Services&nbsp;</strong><br />
			The services offered by SETC include:</p>

			<ul>
				<li>Assess and analyse internship requirements put forth by employers&nbsp;</li>
				<li>Source for interns from acceptable institutions in desired country&nbsp;</li>
				<li>Introduce and arrange for interviews by employers</li>
				<li>Assist employers in application of training work passes</li>
				<li>Provide arrival services to interns on airport reception, accommodation, medical check-up, MOM documentation, etc.</li>
				<li>Provide settlement services to interns including briefing on Do&rsquo;s and Don&rsquo;ts of Singapore, opening of bank account, transport orientation, lifestyle adaptation. etc.</li>
				<li>Provide work assessment and mentoring, conflict resolution and counselling to interns.</li>
				<li>Arrange internship evaluation report and certificate from employers at end of internship.</li>
				<li>Provide departure services to interns including air ticket booking and sending off at airport.</li>
			</ul>

			<p>For most updated information on internship in Singapore, kindly refer to&nbsp;<a href="http://www.mom.gov.sg/">www.mom.gov.sg</a>.</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
